        },
        {
          "username": "Caleb Eggensperger",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "105936729075129336157",
          "user_review_count": 32,
          "user_photo_count": 11,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKLso2lfdhtY6uTUgBolfUnNvCGwG5MvZqIqSdqhXuKGyM9FeL2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "A baffling monument to the downfall of capitalism. A decaying, lifeless husk of a convenience store with signs everywhere saying to check expiration dates (because they don't want to pay employees to do so), broken, dirty tiles underfoot, pharmacy line that takes half an hour to get through if you're lucky. All wrapped up inside a beautiful old bank. Really sad. Makes me depressed every time I have to go in. Employees are doing their best, but they're clearly stretched too thin by a failing $100B company that just cares about profits over people.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21oYU9UbFdORnBvU0hGc1MxbHZOVjlrU0hWSFRFRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x2cc1b72ca3975eda!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOmhaOTlWNFpoSHFsS1lvNV9kSHVHTEE%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "7 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2025-10-31T14:24:22+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "S",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "106491485305867223871",
          "user_review_count": 18,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKd5ItyY9YpCzaKb2btQ4JY5YjJTVPDkzFn8MM3VRbvf_30Mw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "This CVS might not always look like the nicest from the outside, but the pharmacy staff are truly exceptional. Clayton consistently provides the best customer service I\u2019ve ever experienced. Today, while I was waiting on a prescription, I overheard him helping other customers and he gave each of them the same excellent care and attention that he always gives me. I even heard one person say to him, \u201cYou made my day.\u201d It\u2019s clear he gets along so well with everyone and he remembers so many of us.\n\nI learned that Clayton is leaving soon for a new job, and while it\u2019s a big loss for the CVS team, I\u2019m so happy for him. Congratulations again and best of luck! Thankfully, there are still other great people, like the amazing pharmacist Sue who got on the phone to help secure the medication I needed, and another kind young woman who\u2019s always been helpful whenever I pick up a prescription.\n\nToday reminded me just how great some people can be. Thank you for being the highlight of so many customers\u2019 days!",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT210dlpuUnhlRTAwTjNJeU5uTTNhRmRNT1dsWU0wRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x2cc1b72ca3975eda!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOmtvZnRxeE00N3IyNnM3aFdMOWlYM0E%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "11 months ago",
